{{en/Community/Junctionary/Navigation}}
The Tightlong junction is useful when you need a non-collision junction and you don't have too much vertical space available.

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/Tightlong.jpeg|thumb|450px|none]]

==Pros==
* Directs trains fast.
* Can handle up to 8 trains.
* Takes up a small amount of vertical space.

==Cons==
* Takes up a large amount of horizontal space.
* Sharp turns.
* Trains must turn right to go left.


